# DaisyUI Usage Rule

## Core Principle
We are using DaisyUI v5. Always use DaisyUI components when possible, and use its theme classes.

## Implementation Details
- Prefer DaisyUI components over custom implementations
- Use DaisyUI's semantic color classes (primary, secondary, accent, etc.)
- Leverage DaisyUI's utility classes for spacing, typography, and layout
- Follow DaisyUI's component patterns and naming conventions

## Examples

### Good ✓
```astro
<button class="btn btn-primary">Click me</button>
<div class="card bg-base-200 shadow-xl">
  <div class="card-body">
    <h2 class="card-title">Card title</h2>
  </div>
</div>
```

### Bad ✗
```astro
<!-- Don't create custom button styles when DaisyUI provides them -->
<button class="px-4 py-2 bg-blue-500 text-white rounded">Click me</button>
```

## Component Reference
- Buttons: btn, btn-primary, btn-secondary, btn-accent
- Cards: card, card-body, card-title, card-actions
- Forms: input, select, textarea, checkbox, radio
- Layout: drawer, navbar, footer, hero
- Data display: table, badge, avatar, progress

## Theme Classes
- Colors: primary, secondary, accent, neutral, base-100/200/300
- States: hover:, focus:, active:
- Sizes: btn-xs, btn-sm, btn-md, btn-lg